ength >= 2\n4. Config includes `searchIndexPath: '/search-index.json'` when `search-index.json` exists in output\n5. Config includes content routes -- `routes.filter(r => r.handler === 'static')` has correct count matching HTML output entries\n6. Default port is `3000`\n7. Handles missing `asset-pipeline` data gracefully -- `assetPaths` is `[]`\n\n**DevServerConfig interface** (defined in test file):\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Plugin Dependency Graph (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no dependencies):\n  1. markdown-ext\n  2. asset-pipeline\n  3. syntax-highlight\n  4. taxonomy\n\nWave 2 (depend on Wave 1):\n  5. rss-feed        -> depends on: markdown-ext, taxonomy\n  6. search-index    -> depends on: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight\n\nWave 3 (depend on Wave 2):\n  7. sitemap          -> depends on: taxonomy, rss-feed\n  8. dev-server       -> depends on: asset-pipeline, search-index\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of What Each Plugin Must Export and Do\n\n| Plugin | Factory Function | Hooks Used | Key Data Produced |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **markdown-ext** | `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` | `transformContent` | Converts markdown to HTML; handles `[^N]` footnotes, `:::type` admonition containers |\n| **asset-pipeline** | `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` | `transformContent` | Rewrites `./file` to `/assets/file` in src/href attrs; stores `{ assets: string[] }` at `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` |\n| **syntax-highlight** | `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` | `transformContent` | Adds `highlighted` class and `data-language` attr to `<pre><code class=\"language-X\">` blocks |\n| **taxonomy** | `createTaxonomyPlugin()` | `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild` | Builds `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` at `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`; generates `tags/{tag}.html` pages; normalizes tags to lowercase |\n| **rss-feed** | `createRssFeedPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | Generates `feed.xml` (RSS 2.0); items sorted newest-first; CDATA-wrapped content; uses taxonomy data for `<category>` tags |\n| **search-index** | `createSearchIndexPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | Generates `search-index.json`; entries have `{ slug, title, content (plain text), tags? }` |\n| **sitemap** | `createSitemapPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | Generates `sitemap.xml`; includes all output entries as `<url><loc>` with `baseUrl` prefix |\n| **dev-server** | `createDevServerPlugin()` | `afterBuild` | Stores `DevServerConfig` at `ctx.data['dev-server-config']`; port 3000; routes for static/asset/search; reads `asset-manifest` and `search-index.json` |\n\nAll plugins must implement the `Plugin` interface with `name`, `version`, `dependencies` (array of dependency plugin names), and `hooks`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a531a05 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 35847\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 87494</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d54179d9-bde0-4fa6-ba3e-b433168874e3","uuid":"c7cf1697-6592-4c62-bb3f-6ee328641bd0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase thoroughly. I need:\n1. Full directory structure\n2. Contents of ALL files in src/core/ (types.ts, templates, build engine, etc.)\n3. Contents of ALL test files in tests/ (both core.test.ts and everything in tests/plugins/)\n4. package.json, tsconfig.json, and any config files\n5. Any existing files in src/plugins/\n\nBe very thorough - read every file completely. I need to understand the Plugin interface, all type definitions, and every test expectation.","agentId":"a531a05","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete codebase analysis.\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .eslintrc.cjs\nâ”śâ”€â”€ .gitignore\nâ”śâ”€â”€ TASK.md\nâ”śâ”€â”€ package.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ package-lock.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ tsconfig.json\nâ”śâ”€â”€ vitest.config.ts\nâ”śâ”€â”€ src/\nâ”‚   â”śâ”€â”€ core/\nâ”‚ 