string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n**Key observations about the Plugin interface:**\n- `name`: string identifier\n- `version`: semver string\n- `dependencies`: array of plugin names (used for topological sort)\n- `hooks`: object with three optional hooks: `beforeBuild`, `transformContent`, `afterBuild`\n\n### `/workspace/src/core/engine.ts` -- BuildEngine\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class:\n1. **`registerPlugin(plugin)`** -- pushes plugin to internal array\n2. **`registerTemplate(template)`** -- stores template by name in a Map\n3. **`resolvePluginOrder()`** -- topological sort using DFS; throws `\"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"` or `\"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"`\n4. **`build(files)`** -- the main pipeline:\n   - Creates `BuildContext` with copies of files and empty Maps for output/assets/data\n   - Runs `beforeBuild` hooks in dependency order\n   - Runs `transformContent` hooks in dependency order (each plugin transforms ALL files before next plugin runs)\n   - Renders templates: for each file, looks up `file.template` (or `'default'`), calls `template.render()`, stores in `ctx.output` as `{slug}.html`; if no matching template, stores raw content\n   - Runs `afterBuild` hooks in dependency order\n   - Returns the `BuildContext`\n5. **`getPlugins()`** / **`getTemplates()`** -- return copies\n\n### `/workspace/src/core/templates.ts` -- Templates\n\nTwo factory functions:\n- **`createDefaultTemplate()`** -- wraps content in `<article>` with `<h1>`, optional `<time>`, and `<div class=\"content\">`\n- **`createListTemplate()`** -- wraps content in `<div class=\"list\">`\n\nBoth include `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<html>`, `<head>` with title `\"{title} | {siteTitle}\"`.\n\n### `/workspace/src/core/index.ts` -- Re-exports\n\nExports `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all type interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## Test Files\n\n### `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts` -- 15 tests for BuildEngine\n\nTests cover: register plugins, register templates, build with default template, build with list template, raw content when no template, beforeBuild hook, transformContent hook, afterBuild hook, dependency order resolution, circular dependency error, missing dependency error, multiple plugins in order, shared data store, file metadata retention, empty file list.\n\n### Plugin Test Files (60 tests total, 8 files)\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` -- 8 tests\n**Factory**: `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`\n**Import**: `../../src/plugins/markdown-ext.js`\n**Hook used**: `transformContent`\n**Tests**:\n1. Converts basic markdown to HTML -- expects `<h1>`, `Hello`, `<strong>bold</strong>`\n2. Handles footnotes `[^1]` syntax -- expects `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n3. Renders footnote section at bottom -- expects `<section class=\"footnotes\">`, `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>`, `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>`\n4. Converts `:::note` to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n5. Converts `:::warning` to `<div class=\"admoni